org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.model

Class PackageOntology

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.dataconservancy.packaging.tool.model.PackageOntology

  • public class PackageOntology
extends Object
    Package Ontologies define the set of artifacts, properties, and relationships within a PackageDescription, as well as the fundamental domain constraints among them.

      • addArtifactProperty

        public void addArtifactProperty(String artifactType,
                                String propertyName,
                                String valueType,
                                int minOccurrence,
                                int maxOccurrence,
                                boolean isSystemSupplied,
                                boolean isInheritable)
        Adds an allowable property to existing Artifact Type. If the Artifact Type specified in the argument does not exist in the ontology instance, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        artifactType - The Artifact Type which this property can be associated with.
        propertyName - the property name
        valueType - Simple types, such as String, integer, DateTime, etc.
        minOccurrence - the minimal occurrence count for this property.
        maxOccurrence - the maximum occurrence count for this property.
        isSystemSupplied - A flag denoting whether the property is supplied by the system, false if the user provides the property
        isInheritable - A flag denoting whether or not the value of the property can be inherited by children of the artifact

      • addArtifactRelationship

        public void addArtifactRelationship(String artifactType,
                                    String relationshipName,
                                    String relatedArtifactType,
                                    boolean isHierarchical,
                                    int minOccurrence,
                                    int maxOccurrence)
        Adds an allowable relationship to existing Artifact Type. If the Artifact Type specified in the argument does not exist in the ontology instance, IllegalArgumentException will be thrown
        Parameters:
        artifactType - The Artifact Type which this relationship can be associated with
        relationshipName - Name of relationship
        relatedArtifactType - The Type of Artifact that can be related to the given Artifact Type via this relationship.
        minOccurrence - the minimal occurrence count for this relationship.
        maxOccurrence - the maximum occurrence count for this relationship.
        isHierarchical - A flag denoting that the relationship contains heirarchical information between two artifact.

      • getPropertyType

        public String getPropertyType(String artifactType,
                              String complexPropertyName,
                              String propertyName)
        Gets the type of the given property on the given artifact, or null if the property doesn't exist on the artifact.
        Parameters:
        artifactType - The type of the artifact that contains the property.
        propertyName - The name of the property to retrieve the type from.
        complexPropertyName - The name of the complex property the property belongs to, or null if it doesn't belong to a complex property.
        Returns:
        The type name of the property, or null if the property isn't found on the artifact.
